The paper discusses the implementation of Binarized Neural Networks on hardware, which falls under the category of Embedded Systems (cs.ET). The paper also involves the use of stochastic computing, which is a topic in Computer Architecture (cs.AR) and Neural Networks (cs.NE). The simulations are performed on image datasets, which are commonly used in Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the scheme using Spin Torque Magnetoresistive Random Access Memory, which is a topic in Systems and Control (cs.SY).
